Trim the @carrot{1}, then quarter lengthways (no need to peel). Chop widthways into
small pieces. Trim the root and the dark green leafy part from the @leek{1}. Slice
into rounds about 1/2 cm thick. Halve the @red chilli{1/2} lengthways, remove the
seeds then finely chop.

Pick both the @thyme{1/2} leaves and the @sage{1/2} leaves from their stalks
(discard the stalks from both herbs.) Roughly chop the sage leaves.

Heat a splash of @oil{1%splash} in a large #saucepan{} over medium heat. Add the
carrot, leek, a pinch of chilli (add more or less depending on how much you like
spice!) and all of the thyme and sage. Season with @salt{} and cook gently until
soft, ~{8-9%minutes}, stirring occasionally.

> Turn the heat down if the ingredients start to brown.

Meanwhile, place each @skin-on British chicken breasts{2} between two sheets of
#clingfilm{}. Bash with the bottom of a saucepan or a #rolling pin{} until just
under 1cm thick all over. Heat a splash of @oil{1%splash} in a #frying pan{} on
medium-high heat. Season both sides of the chicken with @salt{} and
@ground black pepper{}, then lay in your pan, skin-side down.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat.

Cook for around ~{5-6%minutes} on each side.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While the chicken cooks, drain and rinse the @lentils{1} in a #sieve{}. Once the
veggies are soft, add the lentils along with a splash of water, @chicken stock
powder{1} and @reduced fat creme fraiche{112.5%g}. Stir to dissolve the stock
powder, bring to the boil and then remove from the heat. Season to taste with
@salt{} and @ground black pepper{} if needed. Add more chilli if you want it spicier!

Spoon the spiced creamy lentils onto your plates and top with the pan-fried
chicken. Enjoy!